										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>One characteristic all successful marketers seem to share is curiosity. You‚Äôre always on the hunt for the next big idea or tactic to try.</p>
<p>Marketing newsletters are a great source of info to feed that curiosity. So, I asked a bunch of marketers which ones they loved most.</p>
<p>I filtered out newsletters from big-name marketing gurus (sorry, Seth Godin). That way, you‚Äôd only get options that share ground-level, relatable strategies to use in your everyday work.</p>
<p>I also reached out to several of the newsletter authors to get a little behind-the-scenes scoop about what they write and who it‚Äôs for. That‚Äôll help you decide which are most worthy of your valuable time.</p>
