<div id="8-of-the-best-newsletters-for-marketers"></div>
<h2>8 of the best marketing newsletters out there</h2>
<p>The list of recommended <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/25/email-newsletter-ideas">marketing newsletters</a> ended up being nicely well-rounded. There are options for marketing niches like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/08/content-creator">content creators</a> as well as big-picture publications for all you <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/10/28/growth-strategy">growth gurus</a>.</p>
<div id="contentious"></div>
<h3>1. Contentious: Best for learning how to make your mark as a content marketer</h3>
<p><a href="https://linktr.ee/asklaurenlang" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contentious</a>, besides having a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/01/05/creative-newsletter-names">cool name</a>, is a quickly digestible <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-write-a-newsletter">monthly newsletter</a> by content marketer and coach <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/asklaurenlang/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lauren Lang</a>. It focuses on helping content marketers show the value of their work, both to their teams and personally.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-contentious-png.webp" alt="Marketing newsletters - Contentious screenshot." width="776" height="759" class="aligncenter wp-image-89864 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-contentious-png.webp 776w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-contentious-480x469.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 776px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>You have to love a writer who can build a hook around hot dog water.</em></p>
<p>‚Äú<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/18/content-marketing-examples">Content marketing</a> is in a really precarious position at most companies. It can be misunderstood. Not just by senior leadership, but by your own marketing peers,‚Äù Lauren said. ‚ÄúWe are more cross-functional and less transactional than a lot of marketing functions, and sometimes even marketing leaders don&#8217;t know what to do with us.‚Äù</p>
<p>This topic can get a bit existential at times. But Lauren breaks it down into bite-sized bits and presents them so readers have an actionable takeaway. ‚ÄúEach issue includes three sections on a topic like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/customer-data">using data</a> or working with SMEs: an actionable tip, an anti-pattern like a major misconception or common mistake, and a big idea that tackles a more philosophical angle,‚Äù she explained.</p>
<p>Personally, I love how vulnerable and transparent Lauren is in her writing. Many content marketers struggle with connecting the dots between a blog or social media post and a line item on the revenue report. Lauren shares her own journey, making the tips feel more personal and rooted in experience.</p>
<h4>The past issue you need to read</h4>
<p>The C-suite aren‚Äôt the only people who may miss the value of content marketing. Sometimes, it‚Äôs your own customers. In <a href="https://asklaurenlang.substack.com/p/3-i-can-see-for-miles" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this issue of Contentious</a>, Lauren hilariously shows how her tough <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">target audience</a>‚Äîengineering leaders‚Äîoften spurns any attempts at connection. Then, she shares how she‚Äôs working to get them on board.</p>
<div id="toms-marketing-ideas">
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4e3.png" alt="üì£" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Calls to action are critical for marketing newsletter success.</strong> Download <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download">The 42 Best Call to Action Phrases Ever (&amp; Why They Work)</a></p>
</div>
<h3>2. Tom‚Äôs Marketing Ideas: Best for quick-win marketing tactics with a short time-to-value</h3>
<p>Each week, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tomorbach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tom Orbach</a> sends a new marketing tip to the subscribers of <a href="https://www.marketingideas.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tom‚Äôs Marketing Ideas</a>. What you‚Äôll quickly notice when you read an issue of his newsletter is that every idea is something you can<em> sit down and actually do</em> right away.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-toms-marketing-ideas-png.webp" alt="Marketing newsletters - screenshot from Tom's Marketing Ideas." width="779" height="853" class="aligncenter wp-image-89865 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-toms-marketing-ideas-png.webp 779w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-toms-marketing-ideas-480x526.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 779px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Tom gets right down to business in each issue of Tom‚Äôs Marketing Ideas.</em></p>
<p>‚ÄúI started Marketing Ideas with a simple rule: if something can&#8217;t be implemented within a week, it doesn&#8217;t make the cut,‚Äù he told me.</p>
<p>Tom covers a wide swath of marketing territory in Marketing Ideas. Scroll through past posts, and you‚Äôll see dumb (but useful) career hacks, a three-second hook trick, and tips on picking the perfect color for your next promotion.</p>
<p>I really like that the tactics Tom shares aren‚Äôt just amorphous thoughts from the top of his head. ‚ÄúEvery Friday, I share one powerful marketing tactic that&#8217;s been battle-tested by real companies, broken down into an actionable playbook,‚Äù he said.</p>
<h4>The past issue you need to read</h4>
<p>If you want to get a feel for just how tactical Tom‚Äôs newsletter is, read <a href="https://www.marketingideas.com/p/the-billion-dollar-support-ticket" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this issue</a> about leveraging your customer support inbox for million-dollar marketing ideas. It packs several real-world examples and a multi-step playbook into a 90-second read.</p>
<div id="growth-unhinged"></div>
<h3>3. Growth Unhinged: Best for getting real-life growth tactics from the smartest startups</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre looking for a deep dive into the go-to-market (GTM) strategies of the fastest-growing startups, <a href="https://www.growthunhinged.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Growth Unhinged</a> by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kyle-poyar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kyle Poyar</a> should be in your inbox.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-1024x833.webp" alt="Marketing newsletters - screenshot from Growth Unhinged." width="1024" height="833" class="aligncenter wp-image-89866 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-1024x833.webp 1024w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-300x244.webp 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-768x625.webp 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-1080x879.webp 1080w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-980x797.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-480x391.webp 480w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-growth-unhinged-png.webp 1138w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p>Each issue of Growth Unhinged features a massive missive written by a different marketing or growth leader. They cover topics like GTM automation, product-led growth failures, and winning over a skeptical company board.</p>
<p>Having a different guest writer for each issue means readers get new perspectives and hard-won knowledge from real-world experience. Kyle says he‚Äôs along for the same ride. ‚ÄúWriting Growth Unhinged is my own professional development, letting me learn from the sharpest software founders and leaders on the planet.‚Äù</p>
<p>I‚Äôve read several issues of Growth Unhinged, and it‚Äôs incredible how informative each one is. I‚Äôm amazed that Kyle gets these very busy thought leaders to provide so much of their playbook in such detail.</p>
<h4>The past issue you need to read</h4>
<p>In the midst of our current <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-in-marketing">AI</a> euphoria, it feels like the right move is to prominently promote your newest product as ‚ÄúAI-powered‚Äù or ‚ÄúAI-enabled.‚Äù In <a href="https://www.growthunhinged.com/p/ai-messaging-study" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this issue of Growth Unhinged</a>, the co-founder and CEO of Irrational Labs says that decision might turn your audience off‚Äîand she has new data to prove it.</p>
<div id="tinkering-with-ideas"></div>
<h3>4. Tinkering with Ideas: Best for learning how to automate and improve your workflow</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annabyang/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anna Burgess Yang</a> is a content marketer who‚Äôs becoming known for her expertise in creating and automating marketing workflows. If that sounds a little techy, Anna‚Äôs<a href="https://tinkeringwithideas.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Tinkering with Ideas</a> newsletter will bring it back down to earth.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-1024x813.webp" alt="Marketing newsletters - screenshot from Tinkering with Ideas." width="1024" height="813" class="aligncenter wp-image-89867 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-1024x813.webp 1024w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-300x238.webp 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-768x610.webp 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-1080x858.webp 1080w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-980x778.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-480x381.webp 480w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/marketing-newsletters-wordstream-tinkering-png.webp 1199w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Tinkering with Ideas is full of easy automation how-to guides.</em></p>
<p>‚ÄúI share a lot of ‚Äòtips and tricks‚Äô online, like apps I use, things I‚Äôve read, or something that makes me smile,‚Äù Anna said. ‚ÄúI thought other people might like a short newsletter of quick and easy ways to make their days better.‚Äù</p>
<p>Even Anna&#8217;s method for curating new ideas is a lesson in operational efficiency. &#8220;<span>I save ideas all the time,&#8221; she said. &#8220;Maybe it‚Äôs something in my everyday life that I find useful or an app I recently checked out. I store all of my ideas in Trello. My newsletters often have a theme, so I‚Äôll find three ideas that are related to each other (even loosely), and those become a future issue.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>Past issues detail several ways to cut out busy work from your processes. For example, Anna wrote how to automatically send published articles to Buffer, how to organize research in Google Docs, and automation tips for audio and video files.</p>
<h4>The past issue you need to read</h4>
<p>As her <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/01/05/creative-newsletter-names">newsletter title</a> suggests, Anna tinkers with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-copywriting-tools">tech tools</a> so you don‚Äôt have to. This <a href="https://tinkeringwithideas.io/automatically-add-substack-subscribers-to-kit/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">issue of Tinkering with Ideas</a> is a great example. In it, she explains how she created a way to automatically add Substack subscribers to her <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/01/email-marketing-tips">email marketing</a> platform Kit (formerly Convertkit).</p>
<div id="the-lunch-break">
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a5.png" alt="üí•" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Free resource!</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/growth-strategies?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_GrowthStrategy_Download">7 Steps to a Growth Strategy that Gets Results</a></p>
