		<item>
		<title>How to Write an Introduction Email (+Templates &#038; Examples)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/introduction-email</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kristen McCormick]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Feb 2024 12:30:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Email Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=79798</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>For when you need a more professional greeting than "What's up?"</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/introduction-email">How to Write an Introduction Email (+Templates &#038; Examples)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Expanding your skillset, entering into a new field, getting a great job, growing your business‚Äîthese are all great things. But they all will involve, at some point or another, introducing yourself to new people. After all, you can‚Äôt grow if you don‚Äôt step out past your current circles.</p>
<p>Enter the introduction email. The building block of every great career, network, and business. So how do you write an introduction email that gets a response? That makes a good first impression?</p>
<p>In this post, I‚Äôm going to share some easy tips to write a great introduction email and then provide examples and templates for six different scenarios.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#how-to-write-an-introduction-email">How to write an introduction email</a></li>
<li><a href="#career-networking-introduction-email">Career networking introduction email</a></li>
<li><a href="#business-networking-introduction-email">Business networking introduction email</a></li>
<li><a href="#connection-introduction-email">Introduction email connecting two people</a></li>
<li><a href="#sales-email-after-content-download">Sales email after content download</a></li>
<li><a href="#sales-prospecting-introduction-email">Sales prospecting intro email</a></li>
<li><a href="#business-to-business-introduction-email">Business-to-business introduction email</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="how-to-write-an-introduction-email"></div>
<h2>How to write an introduction email</h2>
<p>There are lots of different scenarios where you‚Äôll need to introduce yourself or others, but there are a few key fundamentals when it comes to writing an introduction email that apply across the board.</p>
<h3>Keep it brief</h3>
<p>Unless you‚Äôre pouring out your soul to a dear friend, NO emails should be long. Not <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/01/email-marketing-tips">marketing emails</a>. Not sales emails. Not introduction emails. Period! Think of your introduction email as the ad and the subsequent meeting or phone call as the product. It needs to have enough detail to capture interest while being brief enough to inspire a response.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-tip-keep-brief.webp" alt="introduction email tip example of brief email" width="936" height="479" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79802" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-tip-keep-brief.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-tip-keep-brief-480x246.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.leadloft.com/blog/emails-in-spam" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>Be clear with your purpose</h3>
<p>This is an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/01/03/email-marketing-best-practices">email best practice</a> for any scenario. No matter what the introduction is, you are reaching out because they have something that you want. And that‚Äôs okay. Be clear that you are reaching out because you are in X position/scenario looking for Y, and that they have Y. Giving this context directly will help keep the email short and make it easy for the recipient to digest‚Äîand respond to‚Äîquickly.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4e8.png" alt="üì®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want more help with your email marketing? <strong>Get the guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteEmailExampleTemplate.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Email_EmailTemplates_Download">The Complete Email Marketing Toolkit</a></p>
<h3>Make a specific ask</h3>
<p>‚ÄúI‚Äôd love to pick your brain‚Äù is not specific enough. Neither is ‚ÄúWould you be open to a conversation?‚Äù Be specific with the time frame, mode of communication, and even the purpose, and frame it as a yes or no. For example, ‚ÄúI have some questions about [topic] and would love to hear your insights. Would you be available for a phone or Zoom call next week?‚Äù</p>
<h3>Include a detail about them</h3>
<p>At the heart of every introduction email is a request for that person‚Äôs time. Time to read the email, time to meet with you, and so on. You can (and should) ask about ways to return the favor for them once you‚Äôve met, but you can pay it forward a bit just by taking the time to learn about them beforehand and including it in your email.</p>
<p>This is NOT flattery. Simply saying ‚ÄúI noticed X‚Äù implies on its own that you were impressed without making it sound like ‚ÄúI am flattering you so that you‚Äôll meet with me.‚Äù</p>
<h2>Introduction email templates and examples</h2>
<p>Here are some introduction examples and templates for a range of purposes that incorporate the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/25/email-copywriting-tips">email copywriting tips</a> I‚Äôve shared.</p>
<div id="career-networking-introduction-email"></div>
<h3>Introduction email #1: Career networking outreach</h3>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: [Relevant connection/topic of interest]</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>My name is Kristen McCormick and I [found you on X/was referred to you by X]. [Statement about yourself that gives context about why you are reaching out]. [Say something specific about their specific value/achievements]. Would you have time for a phone or Zoom conversation with me this week? I‚Äôd love to ask some questions about your experience [for X purpose] and learn also if there are any ways in which I can be of help to you.</p>
<p>If so, feel free to drop some day and times that work for you and I can send you a calendar invite.</p>
<p>Thanks!<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: Dartmouth alumni / content marketing</p>
<p>Hi Garett,</p>
<p>My name is Kristen and found you while searching on LinkedIn for fellow Dartmouth alums who are in the marketing field. I am currently in marketing operations but looking to move more into a content focus, and I noticed that you have a range of content experience, from ads and email to SEO and even design work. Would you have time for a phone or Zoom conversation with me this week? I‚Äôd love to ask some questions about your experience that might help guide my path, and learn also if there are any ways in which I can be of help to you.</p>
<p>If so, feel free to drop some day and times that work for you and I can send you a calendar invite.</p>
<p>Thanks!<br />
Kristen</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-career-networking.webp" alt="career networking introduction email example" width="1002" height="1100" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79804" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-career-networking.webp 1002w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-career-networking-980x1076.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-career-networking-480x527.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1002px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Note that we have plenty of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/10/26/networking-email-subject-lines-templates">networking email templates and subject lines here</a>.</p>
<div id="business-networking-introduction-email"></div>
<h3>Introduction email example #2: Business networking outreach</h3>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: Reaching out via [person who referred you]</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>My name is [Name] and I was given your name by [Name] of [relevant origin]. I am [state what you are trying to accomplish] and am looking to talk with others who have successfully done so‚Äîand I can see that you have! [State specific detail you appreciated about them.]</p>
<p>Would you have any time this week for a phone or Zoom call? I‚Äôd love to learn about your path in general and get your insights on some questions I have.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre available, let me know what days or times work for you and I‚Äôll send you a calendar invite. Thank you!</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: Reaching out via Valorie Jackson</p>
<p>Hi Leslie,</p>
<p>My name is Susan Moor and I was given your name by Valorie Jackson of NASM. I am in the process of starting my own senior move management business (Clear Paths for Seniors) and am looking to talk with others who have successfully done so‚Äîand I can see that you have! I also found that the ‚ÄúMy philosophy‚Äù page on your website resonated with me. Would you have any time this week for a phone or Zoom call? I‚Äôd love to learn about your path in general and get your insights on some questions I have.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre available, let me know what days or times work for you and I‚Äôll send you a calendar invite. Thank you!</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br />
Susan</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-business-networking.webp" alt="business networking introduction email example" width="970" height="1008" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79805" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-business-networking.webp 970w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-business-networking-480x499.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 970px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f495.png" alt="üíï" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want more tips and ideas? We&#8217;ve got a whole lot for you! <strong>Get the guide &gt;&gt;</strong> 130+ of the Best <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteBestOnlineMarketingTips.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_130marketingtips_Download">Online Marketing Tips for Generating More Traffic, Leads, &amp; Sales</a></p>
<div id="connection-introduction-email"></div>
<h3>Introduction email example #3: Introducing two people</h3>
<p>Note that with this type of introduction, you can be more on the ‚Äúflattery‚Äù side, as you‚Äôre trying to convey to each person quickly why it‚Äôs worth their time to connect with the other.</p>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: [Name] &lt;&#8211;&gt; [Name]</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>I‚Äôd like to introduce you to [Name], [include relevant details/highlights about this person]. [He/she] is looking for opportunities right now and I immediately thought of [company]!</p>
<p>[Opportunity seeker‚Äôs name], [name] is the [role] at [company]. [Call out relevant details/highlights about this person], and [he/she] is the best person to talk to to see if you might be a fit.</p>
<p>I‚Äôll let you two take it from here!</p>
<p>Best,<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: Justin &lt;&#8211;&gt;Olivia</p>
<p>Hi Justin,</p>
<p>I‚Äôd like to introduce you to Olivia Channing, a content marketer with five years of experience in SEO, SEM, social, email, and more in the B2B space. She is looking for opportunities right now and I immediately thought of Sparkwise!</p>
<p>Olivia, Justin is the Director of Marketing at Sparkwise. He is the mastermind behind all of their great content, and the best person to talk to to see if you might be a fit.</p>
<p>I‚Äôll let you two take it from here!</p>
<p>Best,<br />
Kristen</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-introducing-two-people.webp" alt="introduction email example for introducing two connections" width="1096" height="1098" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79806" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-introducing-two-people.webp 1096w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-introducing-two-people-980x982.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-introducing-two-people-480x481.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1096px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="sales-email-after-content-download"></div>
<h3>Introduction email example #4: Sales email after content download</h3>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: [Goal] made easy</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>I noticed you recently downloaded our [guide name]. The people who find this guide helpful are typically those who are trying to [achieve goal].</p>
<p>If this resonates with you, [business name] may be a great fit for you. [One sentence about how your business solves that problem and why it‚Äôs better than the rest].</p>
<p>Are you free this week to talk about your [area of specialty] goals?</p>
<p>Best,<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: Ad budget optimization made easy</p>
<p>Hi Brianna,</p>
<p>I noticed you recently downloaded our PPC Pro Tips Guide. The people who find this guide helpful are typically those who are trying to reduce wasted spend, stretch their budget further, or both.</p>
<p>If this resonates with you, AdPro may be a great fit for you. It‚Äôs a platform we built specifically for small ad agencies like yours that automates budget optimization using a wider range of data than what‚Äôs available in Google Ads alone.</p>
<p>Are you free this week to talk about your PPC goals?</p>
<p>Best,<br />
Kristen</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales.webp" alt="introduction email example for after content download" width="994" height="1010" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79807" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales.webp 994w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales-980x996.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales-480x488.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 994px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="sales-prospecting-introduction-email"></div>
<h3>Introduction email example #5: Sales prospecting</h3>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: A better way to [achieve goal]</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>I noticed on your website that you‚Äôre using [tool] for [purpose]. While [tool] is great for [persona] looking to [achieve this small goal], it is not suited for [reader‚Äôs persona] [that does this larger function/with this larger goal].</p>
<p>[Your product/business] is built for [the larger function], [acheiving this bigger benefit/goal]. Do you have time this week for a [X-minute demo/call]?</p>
<p>Let me know,<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: A better way to text</p>
<p>Hi Naomi,</p>
<p>I noticed on your website that you‚Äôre using Chatter for business texting. While Chatter is great for small businesses looking to get feedback and reviews, it is not suited for larger businesses that text with customers throughout their journey.</p>
<p>Bizchat is built for multi-channel communication with customers at every stage of the journey, improving funnel retention and ultimately increasing the bottom line. Do you have time this week for a 20-minute demo?</p>
<p>Let me know,<br />
Kristen</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales-prospecting.webp" alt="sales prospecting introduction email example" width="960" height="936" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79808" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales-prospecting.webp 960w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-sales-prospecting-480x468.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 960px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="business-to-business-introduction-email"></div>
<h3>Introduction email example #6: Business to business outreach</h3>
<h4>Template</h4>
<p>Subject line: [Offer] for [Business name]</p>
<p>Hi [name],</p>
<p>My name is [name] and I‚Äôm reaching out to introduce myself and explore opportunities to help strengthen the [company name] brand.</p>
<p>I run my own [industry] agency called [agency name], which specializes in [state your relevant and unique specialty]. I‚Äôve helped several businesses in the [industry] space to [achieve this benefit] and would love to see how I could help you too.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs schedule a call at your convenience to discuss this further. Are you available this week?</p>
<p>Best regards,<br />
[name]</p>
<h4>Example</h4>
<p>Subject line: Video ads for BizMaven</p>
<p>Hi Angela,</p>
<p>My name is Cody and I‚Äôm reaching out to introduce myself and explore opportunities to help strengthen the BizMaven brand.</p>
<p>I run my own video ad agency called CodyReel, which specializes in social video ads with emotional impact. I‚Äôve helped several businesses in the B2B marketing space to elevate their brand and improve ROI, and would love to see how I could help you too.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs schedule a call at your convenience to discuss this further. Are you available this week?</p>
<p>Best regards,<br />
Cody</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-b2b-outreach.webp" alt="business to business introduction email example" width="1076" height="1132" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79809" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-b2b-outreach.webp 1076w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-b2b-outreach-980x1031.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/introduction-email-example-b2b-outreach-480x505.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1076px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Professional introduction emails made easy</h2>
<p>If you‚Äôre looking to grow in life‚Äîwhether that‚Äôs your skill set, your perspectives, your personal brand, or a business, you‚Äôre going to need to tap into resources outside of your network. And you need to take a professional yet personal approach. Master the art of the introduction email using these tips and examples, and you will find yourself building a network, that you can draw from and contribute to, that facilitates your goals!</p>
<p>To write an introduction email, remember:</p>
<ul>
<li>Keep it brief</li>
<li>Be clear with your purpose</li>
<li>Make a specific ask</li>
<li>Include a detail about them</li>
</ul>
<p>Looking for more email writing tips and templates? We‚Äôve got you covered:</p>
<ul>
