										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How to put your customers into a holiday slumber:</p>
<p><em>To our valued customers,</em></p>
<p><em>As the end of the year draws near, we&#8217;d like to take this opportunity to extend a heartfelt thank you to all of you for your support. Thank you for choosing us and we wish you a wonderful holiday season and happy new year!</em></p>
<div data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="2fa8cb4f-0498-4e4e-8ee7-74ac91222be6" data-langcode="en" class="embedded-entity align-center">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sleepy-bored-face.png" alt="sleepy bored face" typeof="foaf:Image" width="500" height="277" class="aligncenter" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>How to Want to send an <em>authentic</em> holiday greeting this year that your customers will actually want to read? This is your cheat sheet!</p>
<p>Read on so you can write a holiday email to your customers that actually means something.</p>
