<div data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="a8e29c04-94a9-4353-9585-4df24846448a" data-langcode="en" class="embedded-entity align-center">
<article>
<h2></h2>
<h2><span>How to use these holiday email templates</span></h2>
<p>This post contains both the copy and creative you can use for your holiday customer appreciation emails. These emails are longer and more personalized‚Äîgreat for your most loyal customers or for businesses with a small client base. If you want shorter, more general copy, head on over to my <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/28/christmas-holiday-greetings-wishes">holiday greetings and messages</a>.</p>
<p>The copy is written below and also pasted into the templates in Canva, which you can access with a free Canva account! <a href="https://www.canva.com/design/DAFS6Zdax_I/xHDp77z3_8atpm-JFddOQA/view?utm_content=DAFS6Zdax_I&amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_source=publishsharelink&amp;mode=preview" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Here&#8217;s the link to the templates in Canva</a>.</p>
<h2><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/free-holiday-email-templates-canva.png" alt="free holiday email templates in canva" width="555" height="502" class="wp-image-68103 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/free-holiday-email-templates-canva.png 555w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/free-holiday-email-templates-canva-480x435.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 555px, 100vw" /></h2>
<h2><span>Holiday customer appreciation email tips</span></h2>
<p><span>In such a short piece of content as this, small details have big effects. Here&#8217;s how to get it right.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span> </span><span>Keep it short and use a conversational tone. This is an e-toast, not a live journal.</span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Be warm and positive, but not overly hyped. The holidays can be difficult for many people. </span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Make it visual with some graphics or a team photo.</span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Share your growth and achievements to give customers a reason to stay confident in your business.</span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Make it about them. The growth you achieved with their support. Express gratitude!</span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Connect it back to your mission. Not your value prop.</span></li>
<li><span> </span><span>Focus on the future. Speak to an ongoing relationship, but not through a CTA or sales promotion. You can (and should!), however, incorporate CTAs into a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/08/year-in-review-email-examples">year-in-review email.</a></span></li>
</ul>
</article>
</div>
<p><strong>RELATED</strong>: <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/10/christmas-social-media-posts">41 Readymade Holiday Social Media Posts &amp; Canva Templates</a></p>
<h2>5 holiday email templates any business can use</h2>
<p>To make your life easier, I&#8217;ve compiled some templates that incorporate the tips above and the words and phrases lists below. Check&#8217;em out.</p>
<p>If you want to You can also customize them in Canva</p>
